        <h1>Waiting for <strong>upstream</strong> Webservers</h1>

        <div class="content">
            <p>This page is used to test the proper operation of the
            <strong>nginx</strong> HTTP server while we are waiting on upstream
            servers to become ready so that <strong>nginx</strong> can be
            configured as a load balancer. If you can read this page, it means
            that the web server installed at this site is working properly, but
            we are still waiting for usptream webservers.</p>

            <div class="alert">
                <h2>What am I waiting for?</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>You are waiting for webservers to be detected by the policy hub as <strong>ready</strong>. When this happens
                    <tt>/var/cfengine/masterfiles/web_server_ips.dat</tt> on the <strong>policy hub</strong> will contain the ip addresses of the ready webservers. The list of ips found in this file will be used to reconfigure this server as a load balancer. </p>

                    <p>You should now relax, get a cup of coffe, stretch your legs and check back in a few.</p>

